text: Have you seen these ads? They are actually quite mysterious, used for a number of different games, but none of them are the actual one displayed. The thing in the ad seems to be done by some marketing firm as specifically attractive for people to click on, but does not exist...

There is an actual community of people actively trying to search and discover if the game depicted on the ads actually exists somewhere... even some dude trying to make it himself. A bit of an overseen internet rabbit hole that most people miss (unless they are autistic like me)
The fact that there exist illegal numbers is highly fascinating in a weed-epiphany-like fashion

Thinking about Khan Krum... After Byzantine emperor Nikephoros ravaged a Bulgarian city, Krum trapped and literally genocided the entire Byzantine army and had the emperor decapitated, his skull turned into a silver-covered drinking cup for the khan, from which he drank red wine.

Afterwards he tries to make peace, but Byzantines refuse, so he just kinda destroys some city, randomly discovers a bunch of Greek Fire hidden there, and proceeds to sack everything up to Constantinople, in front of which he performs big pagan human and animal sacrifices to ...

frighten the city's inhabitants and governors. 

He planned (and was going to) lay waste to Constantinople, but he suddenly died one night after eating a lot of bear meat. Legends say he had his throat slit by an "invisible hand" and that God punished him for his cruelty.

This kind of proves that paganic people were used as a "punishment" by God for sins. Byzantines were cruel to a Bulgarian city, they got slaughtered - they tried to cheat the khan, he survives and sacks Adrianople. If Byzantines were better Christians this would never happen...

If I have to be truly honest, racism has never appealed to me much. Gypsies have attempted to mug me, and failed to mug me, and have tried to kill me, and have failed to kill me, but I have always had nothing but love in my heart for them. We all play our God-given roles.

Most racism comes from the lack of understanding that different peoples are different. You can not expect a mongol and a pygmy to act the same way, this is madness. You do not hate the goat for being unruly or the Siberian tiger for stalking its prey. We just try our best.
